load blocks by collection
show in ui
init preview by doc
doc to html

.block: unit for building website. update data under this level if editing happened inside
.block.sub: sub-unit for building block or subblock
.block > .inner: block template placed inside
.edit: nodes for editing. should not be translated to doc.
.edit.handle: control buttons (config,remove,drag) for block / subblock / nodes
.edit.insert: for inserting data-repeat nodes

   {attrs: {}, children: {}, content: ""}
  <div data-attr="" class="block sub">  .block - top level block. .block.sub - child block
    <div class="edit handle">...</div> # controller
    <div class="inner">
      ... ( either content or children blocks )
      <div class="edit insert"></div>
    </div>
    
  </div>
